cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.ET, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a three-stage scheme to achieve dispatchability of a system composed of plug-in electric vehicles and intermittent generation, which involves modeling and control of a complex system. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes the use of probabilistic forecasts to address uncertainties inherent to intermittent generation, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The use of probabilistic forecasts involves machine learning techniques such as regression and probabilistic modeling. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper deals with the integration of plug-in electric vehicles and intermittent generation into existing power systems, which is an emerging technology. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may involve software engineering aspects such as simulation and modeling of the system.
